media:group.media:title: STRANDBEEST MIMICRI 2019
media:group.media:description:
Mimicry is an evolved resemblance between an organism and another species. Some hoverflies (Chrysotoxum cautum), for example, keep their enemies away by resembling a wasp.
The Animaris Mimicry here, is a caterpillar that seems to walk on legs. (but he doesn't). The legs do not support the body; they keep the caterpillar inside out of sight. Animaris Mimicry belongs to the family branch of the internet survivors. With legs they survive better on YouTube. Different survival criteria apply on YouTube than on the beach. The beasts on youtube never collapse in the wind…….
